@page "/docs/hover"

<PageTitle>Hover — BlazorMotion</PageTitle>

<div class="breadcrumb">Docs / Gestures / <span>Hover</span></div>
<h1>Hover</h1>
<p>Animate when a pointer (mouse or stylus) enters and leaves an element.</p>

<h2>Usage</h2>
<pre><code>&lt;Motion Tag="div"
        WhileHover="@@(new AnimationProps { Scale = 1.1 })"
        Transition="@@(new TransitionConfig { Type = "spring", Stiffness = 400, Damping = 17 })"&gt;
    Hover me
&lt;/Motion&gt;</code></pre>

<div class="demo-area">
    <Motion Class="demo-box"
            WhileHover="@(new AnimationProps { Scale = 1.15, BackgroundColor = "#7c3aed" })"
            Transition="@(new TransitionConfig { Type = TransitionType.Spring, Stiffness = 400, Damping = 17 })">
        Hover me
    </Motion>
</div>

<h2>Events</h2>
<table class="prop-table">
    <thead><tr><th>Event</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr><td>OnHoverStart</td><td>Fired when pointer enters the element.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>OnHoverEnd</td><td>Fired when pointer leaves the element.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<pre><code>&lt;Motion WhileHover="@@(new AnimationProps { Scale = 1.05 })"
        OnHoverStart="@@(() =&gt; Console.WriteLine("Hover started"))"
        OnHoverEnd="@@(() =&gt;   Console.WriteLine("Hover ended"))"&gt;
    ...
&lt;/Motion&gt;</code></pre>

<div class="callout callout-tip">
    <strong>Note:</strong> Hover uses <code>pointerenter</code>/<code>pointerleave</code> events, so it works with both mouse and pen/stylus input.
</div>
